import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["price"].median():0.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of price?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('symbol').mean()
    data.plot(kind='bar', y='price', legend=False)
    plt.title('What is the average price by symbol?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xlabel('Symbol')
    for i, v in enumerate(data['price']):
        plt.text(i, v, f'{v:.2f}', ha='center', va='bottom')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['date'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['date'].min(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Min date: {data['date'].min().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.axvline(data['date'].max(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Max date: {data['date'].max().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
